reviews.review_text: great show, but... Used to have this on cass., and was really happy to trade for it a few years ago on CDR, only to find that they show had gaps between songs.  Was thrilled to find this site and download, but once again...that gaps are here!  What's the deal!

nothing to report john, the gaps are due to the mp3 format.  get yahoo music engine and download the flac or ogg format.  still haven't figured out the shn files.  this show?  well-played, energetic, but nothing inspired.

Reviewing Please don't attach a 1 star rating because you downloaded MP3's and are diappointed with them.  There is no reason whatsoever to DL an MP3 when you have a lossless file sitting right there for the taking.

This is a good show.

Goodness My first show...15 years old with a head full of acid. The Sugaree, Ramble on Rose and SCORCHING Scarlet>Fire (Garcia's solos in Fire go on and on) are worth the price of download (which is free, which is even better).
a bit overrated good show, vg on paper, good effort, probably wonderful to be there, but honestly not clicking as effortlessly as others did, often struggling a bit. Still good fun.
